cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the inner workings of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and deconvolutional networks (DCNs) for image reconstruction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the encoding and discarding of information in CNNs, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of randomization techniques and empirical evidence suggests a focus on cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
